As we'll see, this is a book that had an extraordinary impact

10
00:00:55,980 --> 00:00:58,320
on two distinct groups.

11
00:00:58,320 --> 00:01:02,640
The first was the Renaissance architectural historian.

12
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:05,670
This book offered a new approach to the way

13
00:01:05,670 --> 00:01:10,920
we understand the architecture of the 15th and the 16th century in Italy.

14
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:14,550
The other group was the modernist architect.

15
00:01:14,550 --> 00:01:17,400
It is strange to think that a book on the Renaissance

16
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:21,270
might have an impact on modernist thinking,

17
00:01:21,270 --> 00:01:26,240
but this book revolutionized our understanding of geometry,

18
00:01:26,240 --> 00:01:29,940
